# üìö Docs or angular.io bug report

### Description

This is a suggestion to make the code for https://angular.io/guide/displaying-data#constructor-or-variable-initialization either warn a reader that copy and paste will generate an error or make the code drop into the example smoothly.

I copy and pasted the code from the **Constructor or variable initialization?** and it did not compile.

Changing the name of the class from AppCtorComponent to AppComponent fixed the error.

Personally, I would prefer showing newbies the error and explaining how to fix it in the guide.  This would serve the purpose of showing what compile errors look like and how to use them in a controlled way. 

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction

### What's the affected URL?**
https://angular.io/guide/displaying-data#constructor-or-variable-initialization

### Reproduction Steps**
>ng new displaying-data
>cd displaying-data/
>rm src/app/app.component.html
>ng serve

- edit app.component.ts to look like...

```
import { Component } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  template: `
  	<h1>{{title}}</h1>
  	<h2>My favorite hero is: {{myHero}}</h2>
  `
})
export class AppCtorComponent {
  title: string;
  myHero: string;

  constructor() {
    this.title = 'Tour of Heroes';
    this.myHero = 'Windstorm';
  }
}
```


### Expected vs Actual Behavior**
Expected the copy and paste to compile.
Actual behavior was an error message.

## üì∑Screenshot
None

## üî• Exception or Error
<pre><code>
ERROR in app.module.ts(5,10): error TS2305: Module '"./app.component"' has no exported member 'AppComponent'.
</code></pre>

